The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Good Morning

 Hello It's Thursday, October 28, 2004

 Road to avoid

 Bagmari Road, from 4 pm to midnight. Processions will be taken out to mark Urush.

 Soiree

 Anjan Dutt and The Music Folk to perform in Poet amp; the Band at Someplace Else, 9 pm.

 Gaan Mela, organised by Dishari, at Howrah Sarat Sadan, 3 pm to 9 pm.

 Stoppard on stage

 The Real Inspector Hound, a play by Tom Stoppard, will be staged by Theatrecian at Gyan Manch, 7 pm.

 Science talk

 Our Friends, the Robots, a lecture-demonstration by scientists Noel and Amanda Sharkey, at British Council, 4 pm.

 Folk dance

 Bedaraas folk dances of Rajasthan and chhau of Purulia will be presented at Bharatiyam, Salt Lake, from 6 pm.

 Art watch

 Bonding ? Unarticulated Parallels in Contemporary Indian Art, an exhibition showcasing works of 55 painters, will be inaugurated by Bikash Bhattacharjee at ITC Sonar Bangla, 7 pm.




